      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOYSTROUS (3) is at the track for the first time. By Tall Dark Stranger and hails from the Alex Ashwood stable. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Has strong trial form coming into this. Makes plenty of appeal. STERLING GIGI (4) added to his recent string of strong performances last start when runner-up over 1720m at Melton, beaten 4 metres. Finds a suitable assignment and will be a major force once more. LOUS  MAMBO (6) is improving with racing, placing last start at Melton. Draws wider but can take another step forward. WICKED TORQUE (1) is a two-year-old filly from the Peter Manning yard on debut. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Was not far away in a recent trial. Finds a nice race so anticipating a bright start to her career.",
